      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "# Wan2.2 Animate — Mix / Character Replacement (RTX 3090 24 GB baseline)\n\nThis is a separate Wan2.2 workflow. Do **not** replace the Wan2.1 SCAIL-2 model inside the SCAIL workflow: SCAIL-2 has its own Wan2.1 architecture and conditioning.\n\n## Default safe test\n- 848 × 480 (both divisible by 16)\n- First 77 frames of the driver clip\n- 6 steps, CFG 1, Euler / Simple\n- Model sampling shift 8\n- Use a 4–5 second, single-person driver clip for the first test.\n\n## Mix mode (default)\nReplaces the tracked person while keeping the original background. Put one green point in the actor using Points Editor, run, inspect the mask preview, then refine points if necessary.\n\n## Move mode\nDisconnect the two links into WanAnimateToVideo: **background_video** and **character_mask**. The reference character will follow the driver's pose and face movement without preserving the source background.\n\nFor a higher-quality pass, first test this default. Then try 8 steps; keep CFG at 1 with the LightX2V LoRA."
      ],
      "title": "Read first",
      "color": "#222",
      "bgcolor": "#000"
    },
